args: So this is your old orphanage, eh?
Seeing it brings back so many memories...
It is good to see you again, Hildegarde.
Yep! Your old childhood pal, in the flesh!
I'm in charge of the orphanage now.
Well, this is a surprise! I had no idea!\nThank you for looking after the place.
No problem. But listen, what brings you\nhere today? And who's that with you?
We're Hildegarde's friends, and we're\nhere to ask for your help.
We are searching for information\nabout her parents.
We thought this would be a good place\nto begin our search.
So you still haven't given up hope, eh?

I remember how you used to just shut
yourself in your room and pray for
them to come while the rest of us
were going about our lives.
I've no desire to relive the past.\nCan you help us or no?
Let me go see if there's anything useful\nin storage. Oh, and it's a mess in there,\nso it might take a while.
You mind playing with the children while\nyou wait? I know they'd love the company.
Hey, lady! Are you gonna play with us?
We would be happy to play with you.\nWhat would you like to do?
Ha ha! Poor Elisanne has no idea\nwhat she's gotten herself into.
They seem almost overjoyed to see us.\nAre visitors really so rare?

They are, I'm afraid. The life of an orphan
here is mostly one of unceasing sameness,
so they tend to latch on to even the
smallest hope of love or salvation.
I know exactly how they feel,\nfor I used to be the same.
Well, most of them seem to be\nwell-adjusted regardless.
Still, there must be some children\nhere who are lonely.
You're right—which makes me wonder\nif I shouldn't be spending my time\nand energy differently.
Should I really be spending all my time\non this self-serving path...?
Sorry, Hildy. I've got a rough idea\nwhere the info you want would be,\nbut like I said, it's a huge mess.
I could use an extra pair of hands\nin there, if you don't mind.
(Is meeting my parents truly what I want?)
Well, according to our new information,\nyour parents should be in this village.
Then let's go find 'em already\nand make a Valentine's miracle!
I mean, there's no better time to tell\nyour parents how you feel.
Are ya gettin' cold feet NOW?
I won't deny there is fear in my heart.\nAfter all, what if they reject me anew?
But there is something I fear even more\nthan that...so I cannot go see them.
My dream was never to MEET them—\nit was for them to come BACK for me.
I wanted them to be the ones who\nreached out to me, not the reverse.
And if I find them in this village today,\nthat dream will become impossible.
The thought of my dream dying—of the\nonly thing I ever truly wanted vanishing\nin a hopeless cloud—terrifies me.
I am so very sorry for saying this after\nall that you have done to help me,\nbut I cannot lie to myself.
Well, if you're sure, we won't push it.\nI'm sorry we couldn't do more.
But I AM happy you felt comfortable\nenough to tell us how you feel.
I was only able to reach this conclusion\nbecause you were all here with me.
I was able to look past my loneliness,\nface my feelings, and find my true wish.
Your TRUE wish? Wait, so there's\nactually something ELSE you want?\nSister, I cannot keep up with you...
You have done too much for me already,\nbut might I ask one more thing of you?
We've come this far, and we'll be with you\nuntil the end. Right, everyone?
Of course. You are very important to us.
Okay, out with it. What's your true wish?
